SIMPLE: nomination
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nomination
<hw>Nom`i*na"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>nominatio</ets>: cf. F. <ets>nomination</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of naming or nominating; designation of a
person as a candidate for office; the power of nominating; the state of
being nominated; <as>as, to win the <ex>nomination</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>nomination</qex> of persons to places being . . . a
flower of his crown, he would reserve to himself.</q>
<rj><qau>Clarendon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The denomination, or name.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Bp. Pearson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nominatival</ent>⟦br⟧
